# Changelog - hypercube-browser-extension

## 2026-01-08 - Description Enhancement (Audit Fix)

### Changed
- **Enhanced description for completeness and discoverability** (auditing-skills workflow)
  - Added missing capabilities: "Firebase deployment", "extension customization", "website generation", "testing", "operational security"
  - Improved searchability: Added "C2 framework" and "red team engagements" industry terms
  - Length: 244 characters (within acceptable range, improved comprehensiveness)

### Removed
- Generic terms: "exploitation framework" → "C2 framework" (more specific)
- Generic terms: "authorized security testing" → "authorized red team engagements" (more discoverable)

### Rationale
- **Completeness**: Original description missed 3 major phases (website, testing, opsec) representing ~40% of workflow content
- **Discoverability**: Users searching for "red team browser extension" or "pentest C2" now find this skill more easily
- **Accuracy maintained**: All described capabilities are present in the skill

### Audit Results
- Phase 1 (Description Format): ⚠️ WARNING → ✅ PASS
- Semantic Review (Completeness): ⚠️ WARNING → ✅ PASS
- Semantic Review (Discoverability): ℹ️ INFO → ✅ PASS

